Package: redelk
Version: 3.0.0
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: python3 (>= 3.8), python3-pip, docker.io (>= 20.10) | docker-ce (>= 20.10), docker-compose-plugin | docker-compose (>= 2.0)
Recommends: curl, wget, openssl, apache2-utils
Maintainer: RedELK Team <redelk@outflank.nl>
Homepage: https://github.com/outflanknl/RedELK
Description: Red Team SIEM - Track and alarm on Blue Team activities
 RedELK is a comprehensive Red Team SIEM (Security Information and Event
 Management) system designed for tracking operations and detecting Blue Team
 investigation activities.
 .
 Features:
  - Modern Python-based installer with interactive wizard
  - Support for multiple C2 frameworks (Cobalt Strike, Sliver, PoshC2)
  - ELK Stack 8.x (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana)
  - BloodHound CE integration
  - Real-time health monitoring
  - Automated certificate generation
  - Comprehensive dashboards and visualizations
 .
 This package provides the main RedELK server installer and management tools.

